chart.description: Number of expired keys for an instance and shards
chart.name: Expired Keys
chart.programText: A = data('expiredkeys*', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'expiredkeys')), rollup='latest').mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: When rss >> used, a large difference means there is memory fragmentation.  When used >> rss, it means part of Redis memory has been swapped off by the operating system: expect some significant latencies
chart.name: Memory Fragmentation Ratio
chart.programText:
A = data('usedmemory', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true')).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('usedmemoryRss', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true')).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = ((B+1)/(A+1)).publish(label='C')

chart.description: Cache hit rate for instance and shards
chart.name: Cache Hit Rate
chart.programText:
A = data('cachehits*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'cachehits')), extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=5).mean(by=['azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).above(0).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('cachemisses*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'cachemisses')), extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=5).mean(by=['azure_resource_id', 'azure_resource_name']).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = ((A) / (A+B) * 100).publish(label='C')

chart.name: Total Keys per Cache
chart.programText: A = data('totalkeys', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true')).mean(by=['azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Cache hit rate for instance and shards
chart.name: Cache Hit Rate Trend
chart.programText:
A = data('cachehits*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'cachehits'))).mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_id', 'azure_resource_name']).above(0).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('cachemisses*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'cachemisses'))).mean(by=['azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = ((A) / (A+B) * 100).publish(label='C')

chart.name: # Connections
chart.programText: A = data('connectedclients', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true')).mean(by=['azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: RSS memory used by each shard
chart.name: Used RSS Memory
chart.programText: B = data('usedmemoryRss*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'usedmemoryRss')), extrapolation='last_value').publish(label='B')

chart.description: Amount of data written to each of the shards
chart.name: Cache Writes
chart.programText: A = data('cacheWrite*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'cacheWrite'))).mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_id', 'azure_resource_name']).publish(label='A')

chart.name: Used Memory
chart.programText: B = data('usedmemory*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'usedmemory')) and (not filter('sf_metric', 'usedmemoryRss*')) and filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis')).publish(label='B')

chart.name: CPU %
chart.programText: A = data('percentProcessorTime*', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'percentProcessorTime'))).mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Number of get commands for an instance and shards
chart.name: Get Commands
chart.programText: A = data('getcommands*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'getcommands')), rollup='sum').mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Server load % for instance and shards
chart.name: Server Load
chart.programText: A = data('serverLoad*', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'serverLoad'))).mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_name']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Number of connections for instance and shards
chart.name: # Connections
chart.programText: A = data('connectedclients*', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'connectedclients'))).mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_name']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Total number of caches including shards
chart.name: # Caches
chart.programText: A = data('cachehits*', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'cachehits'))).count().publish(label='A')

chart.description: # of keys evicted due to hitting max memory limit
chart.name: Evicted Keys
chart.programText: A = data('evictedkeys*', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'evictedkeys'))).sum(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='A')

chart.name: Lowest Cache Hit Rates
chart.programText:
A = data('cachehits', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true'), rollup='average', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=5).mean(by=['azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('cachemisses', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true'), rollup='average', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=5).mean(by=['azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = ((A) / (A+B) * 100).publish(label='C')

chart.description: Number of set commands for an instance and shards
chart.name: Set Commands
chart.programText: A = data('setcommands*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'setcommands')), rollup='sum').mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_id', 'azure_resource_name']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: amount of data read from the each of the shards
chart.name: Cache Reads
chart.programText: A = data('cacheRead*', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'cacheRead')), rollup='average').mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_id', 'azure_resource_name']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Total # of keys in an instance and shards
chart.name: Total Keys
chart.programText: A = data('totalkeys*', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'totalkeys'))).mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Number of commands processed for instance and shards
chart.name: Total Commands Processed
chart.programText: A = data('totalcommandsprocessed*', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'totalcommandsprocessed')), rollup='latest').sum(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).publish(label='A')

chart.name: Total Keys
chart.programText: A = data('totalkeys', filter=filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true')).sum().publish(label='A')

chart.name: Used Memory per Cache
chart.programText: A = data('usedmemory', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true') and (not filter('sf_metric', 'usedmemoryRss*'))).mean(by=['azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).top(count=5).publish(label='A')

chart.name: Server Load %
chart.programText: A = data('serverLoad', filter=filter('resource_type', 'Microsoft.Cache/Redis') and filter('primary_aggregation_type', 'true')).mean(by=['sf_metric', 'azure_resource_name', 'azure_resource_id']).top(count=5).publish(label='A')
